b'Bill Bailey is a true Nebraska hero. I am honored to tell his story. #NEHeroes #ProudNebraskan'
b'Bill was a wonderful husband, brother, son, father. He dedicated quite a bit of his life to helping other people. #NEHeroes'
b'Specialist Bailey earned several military awards including the Purple Heart, Bronze Star, Iraqi Campaign Medal & Combat Action Badge. #Honor'
b'More than one thousand people gathered in Bellevue to remember Bill. #NEHeroes'
b'On May 25, 2007, during a security escort mission, Bill\xe2\x80\x99s vehicle struck an improvised explosive device. Bill Bailey was killed. #NEHeroes'
b'By 2007, the insurgency in Iraq had erupted to new levels of violence. Increased American forces sought to destroy the al Qaeda network.'
b'In 2006, his unit was deployed and assigned to provide security escorts for truck convoys operating out of Balad Air Base in #Iraq.'
b'That deep desire to serve the country continued to tug at him. In 2005, Bill re-enlisted in the @NENationalGuard #Courage'
b'Bill\xe2\x80\x99s protective nature made him a great father. It also made him a great firefighter. #NeHeroes'
b'After 9/11, Bill felt the call to serve his country again. But, first things first. Bill and Dee married in 2004.'
b'In December 2000, Bill met Dee. She was a bank teller at Wells Fargo; he drove an armored truck. They met through a service window.'
b'Bill attended Bellevue East where the call to protect his country prompted him to enlist in the @NENationalGuard in 1995.'

b'He is a true Nebraska hero, and I am honored to tell his story. #SergeantGermaineDebro #NEHeroes'
b'His military decorations include a Bronze Star and a Purple Heart. #Courage'
b'Germaine Debro was promoted posthumously to the rank of sergeant. #NEheroes'
b'On September 18, 2006, the Morning Star Baptist Church near downtown Omaha was filled with people paying a final tribute to Sgt. Debro.'
b'Sergeant Josiah Warren, riding in the right seat, tried unsuccessfully to pull Germaine free. Sgt. Debro died on 9/4/06'
b'Thirty miles outside Baghdad, Germaine\xe2\x80\x99s Humvee struck an improvised explosive device.'
b'On September 4, 2006, a 20-truck convoy headed out from a site 30 miles north of Baghdad.'
b'Germaine\xe2\x80\x99s unit was right in the thick of it. Enemy attacks were frequent. Tensions were high.'
b'After a year of training, the First of the 167th Cavalry arrived in Iraq in early 2006. That\xe2\x80\x99s when the Sunni-Shia civil war erupted.'
b'In 2005, Germaine learned his unit, the First of the 167th Cavalry of the @NEnationalGuard, would deploy to Iraq.'
b'Germaine deployed to Kuwait in 2001 and to Bosnia in 2002. #ProudNebraskan #NEheroes'
b'In 1994, \xe2\x80\x9cG.I. Joe Maine\xe2\x80\x9d followed his calling and enlisted in the #Army and in 1997 joined the @NEnationalguard'
b'Germaine Debro seemed destined for military service. At a young age, he picked up a nick name: \xe2\x80\x9cG.I. Joe Maine.\xe2\x80\x9d #NEheroes'

b'Cpt Yllescas of Osceola, NE is an American hero. It was my honor to tell his story on the Senate floor #NEheroes https://t.co/7gXno8h8GZ'
b'Captain Robert Yllescas embodied the pride of his state, served his country, and loved his family. #ProudNebraskan'
b'Ultimately, Rob\xe2\x80\x99s severe leg and head wounds were too much to overcome. Captain Robert Yllescas died on Dec. 1, 2008.'
b'During Rob\xe2\x80\x99s time at Bethesda Naval Medical Center, President George W. Bush visited him & personally awarded him the #PurpleHeart.'
b'Rob was quickly evacuated out of Afghanistan, stabilized, and moved to the Bethesda Naval Medical Center.'
b'On October 28, 2008, a remotely-controlled IED was detonated and seriously wounded Captain Yllescas.'
b'Rob achieved the rank of #Captain and deployed to Afghanistan in 2008 and stationed at Camp Keating, known to many as dangerous territory.'
b'Returning home to #Nebraska in 2006, Rob continued to excel in the military, later graduating from Army Ranger School. #RangersLeadTheWay'
b'He deployed to Iraq in 2003 for a year & then returned for a 2nd deployment in 2005, when the fighting grew more intense.'
b'In 2001, Rob received his commission as a Second Lieutenant in the @USArmy. #ArmyStrong'
b'At @UNLincoln, he fell in love with his wife Dena and they were married on July 29, 2000.'
b'Rob enrolled in the @NENationalGuard while in college at @UNLincoln with hopes of becoming a general one day. #NEHeroes'
